caption: They offer a large variety of delicious food. I enjoy dining here. Employees are always helpful, rates are affordable and the spot is always clean.

I just finished another take-out order from Pho D'Lite.  They're strictly carry-out now due to the coronavirus, and the staff were all wearing masks and appeared to be keeping a safe distance while working around each other.  The food is excellent.  I've had the pho several times when dining in was an option, now I'm more into the noodle dishes that seem to travel better.  The various bun combinations are all great, rice vermicelli alongside grilled meats and chopped vegetables that give a wonderful range of flavors and textures.  Prices are very reasonable too.  If you haven't tried Pho D'Lite, make a point to grab a meal to-go there.

Once you sit down you have to keep getting up to ask for a drink, or a refill, a box, or the bill. I've never had a server check back and make sure we were good. They are not trained at all and it results in me waiting until "11:01 when we open" or "cant place to-go orders at 845 because we close at 9." I've worked in kitchens all my life and kitchen doesnt close until the restaurant does (unless theres a late night bar.)
